My name is Ayesha Nisar, and I am studying at UAF Sub Campus as a Bachelor’s in Computer Science (BSCS) student. I am passionate about creating innovative technology solutions that can bring positive change to society and improve the lives of people through smart and meaningful digital systems.
I believe technology should not only make systems smarter, but also make human lives better. That belief inspired me to choose my Final Year Project:
“Neuro-Phenotypic Stratification of ASD Risk via Machine Learning”
In Pakistan, awareness about Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) is still very limited. Many children and teenagers remain undiagnosed because families often do not recognize the early signs of autism, and access to professional clinical assessment is difficult, expensive, or unavailable in many areas. As a result, countless individuals do not receive timely support and intervention.
While observing these challenges in our society, I realized that Artificial Intelligence can play an important role in helping healthcare systems identify autism-related risks earlier and more efficiently. This project is not just an academic requirement for my degree — it is a mission that reflects my vision for a healthier, more aware, and more supportive Pakistan.
Through this project, I aim to develop an intelligent AI-assisted triage system that can stratify individuals into clinically relevant ASD risk categories such as High Risk, Moderate Risk, and Low Risk. By using advanced Machine Learning and Deep Learning techniques, the system can assist healthcare professionals in accelerating the referral process for formal clinical assessment and early intervention.
My goal is to contribute toward a future where:
Autism awareness is increased across Pakistan.
Early detection becomes accessible to everyone.
Families receive support at the right time.
Children and teenagers can achieve better developmental outcomes.
Healthcare services become more equitable and technology-driven.
This project combines modern technologies including Python, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, CNNs, GNNs, RNNs, Multi-Modal Data Fusion, FastAPI, Docker, and AI-powered Explainable Risk Stratification to create a smart and impactful healthcare solution.
As a student, researcher, and future AI engineer, I want my work to create real-world impact rather than remain limited to theory. I chose this project because I believe even a small technological contribution can help transform lives and spread awareness in our nation.
I dream of a Pakistan where autism is understood with compassion, identified at an early stage, and supported through intelligent healthcare solutions. This Final Year Project is my step toward that vision.
